# ConfigLoaderSystem

## Purpose
One-shot initialization system. On the first frame, reads `Assets/Engine/Config.json` and creates
EngineConfigSingletonComponent with the UUIDs of the default quad shader, text shader, and font, the 3D
pass resource IDs (`model3DShader`, `render3DTarget` — optional keys naming the flat-unlit model shader
and the offscreen render target the 3D scene draws into), plus
the master/sound/music audio volumes and the default window resolution + display mode (`windowWidth`,
`windowHeight`, `windowMode` — optional keys; default to `1280x720` windowed when absent). It also
reads the UI canvas parameters (`uiReferenceWidth`, `uiReferenceHeight`, `uiMatchFactor` — optional;
default to `1920x1080` reference with a `0.5` match factor when absent), which seed the live UI canvas
in `UIRenderSystem` (ADR 0005). It also reads the text-to-image Generation Config defaults
(`diffusionSteps`, `diffusionCfgScale`, `diffusionSampler`, `diffusionWidth`, `diffusionHeight`,
`diffusionClipSkip` — optional keys that fall back to built-in defaults), which a Generate Image
Request overrides per-call (ADR 0008). No-op on all subsequent frames (presence check guards early
exit).
File reads go through the shared `pg::FileUtils` helpers (also used by `WindowConfigSystem` when it
persists changes).

## Savedata Override
The engine config may declare a `savedataPath` entry pointing at the SaveData folder (a sibling of
Data, `../SaveData` from the working directory). The resolved path is recorded in the component's
`m_SavedataPath` so the runtime (`WindowConfigSystem`) knows where to persist changes. After seeding
the component from the engine config, the system reads `<savedataPath>/Config.json` if it exists and
overlays its entries on top — every field is optional, so a key present in the savedata config
overrides the engine value while absent keys keep the engine value. When `savedataPath` is missing or
the savedata config file does not exist, the engine config values stand unchanged. The savedata file
is the place for user/persisted overrides (e.g. adjusted audio volumes or window resolution) that must
survive without editing the shipped engine config.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Presence-check only; if present, system exits immediately |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Created once from Config.json; contains default shader and font UUIDs, the 3D model shader + render target UUIDs, master/sound/music volumes, default window resolution + mode, UI reference resolution + match factor, the text-to-image Generation Config defaults, and the savedata path |
